Where 
Yijkmn
 is the observed trait value; u is the overall mean; 
ai
 represents the i-level effect of BY; 
bj
 represents the j-level effect of BQ;
dk
 represents the k-level effect of sex; 
hm
 represents the m-level effect of AM; 
eijkmn
 represents the random residual effect. p-values > 0.05 are deemed non-significant, p-values < 0.05 are considered significant, and p-values < 0.01 are highly significant.

